# 1️⃣1️⃣ Best Practices

* Use IRSA instead of node-wide IAM roles
* Use ReadWriteMany only when needed
* Clean unused Access Points
* Monitor EFS costs
* Use Deployment/StatefulSet for production

---

# 1️⃣2️⃣ When to Use EFS

Use EFS when:

* Multiple pods need same storage
* Application must survive pod rescheduling
* You need shared file storage across nodes

Do NOT use EFS when:

* You need high IOPS block storage (use EBS instead)
* Single pod storage is enough

---

# Final Summary

EFS in Kubernetes provides:

* Shared, scalable file storage
* Multi-node access (RWX)
* Automatic Access Point provisioning
* High availability across AZs

But requires:

* Correct IAM permissions
* Proper CSI driver installation
* Correct StorageClass configuration

